olive oil
2 potato
1 carrot
1 Onion
1 stalk celery
40 g butter
2 tbs milk
1 packet beef mince
1 packet Baby Leaves
1 packet garlic paste
1 sachet dried oregano
1 packet tomato paste
½ cup water
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
1 tsp brown sugar
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese

• Boil the kettle. Peel potato and cut into large chunks. Finely chop carrot, onion and celery.
• Half-fill a medium saucepan with boiling water, then add a generous pinch of salt.
• Cook potato in the boiling water, over high heat, until easily pierced with a fork, 12-15 minutes. Drain and return potato to the pan.
• Add the butter and milk to the potato, then season with salt. Mash until smooth.

TIP: Save time and get more fibre by leaving the potato unpeeled.
Little cooks: Get those muscles working and help mash the potatoes!

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over high heat.
• Cook beef mince, breaking up with a spoon, until just browned, 3-4 minutes.

TIP: For best results, drain the oil from the pan before cooking the filling.

• Add carrot, onion and celery to the mince and cook until softened, 4-5 minutes.

• Add baby leaves, garlic paste, dried oregano and tomato paste. Cook until fragrant and wilted, 1 minute.
• Stir in the water, chicken-style stock powder and the brown sugar and cook until slightly thickened, 2-3 minutes.
• Season to taste.

• Preheat grill to medium-high.
• Transfer beef filling to a baking dish. Spread mash over the top. Sprinkle over grated Parmesan cheese.
• Grill pie until mash is golden, 5-10 minutes.

TIP: Grills cook fast, so keep an eye on the pie!
Little cooks: Join in on the fun by smoothing the mash mixture evenly over the pie!

• Divide Italian beef and potato-top pie between plates to serve. Enjoy!